rComments: Michael Carter is a nice guy and I admire his accomplishments as a young prof... but I don't like his teaching style. He makes tough concepts sound easy but then expects you to know them in depth on the test. Questions are purposely worded to make things difficult for you and labs are graded very harshly!!
Not clear with projects and labs. Goes through material too quickly. Tony is much better.
Clear expectation however less experienced than Carlson. Lectures often finished early. Wording of questions was tricky.

Mr. Carter teaches in conjuction with Dr. Carlson. Carter is clear when he presents his information infront of class, however he does expect more out of the students compared to Carlson. Carter focuses more on slide material and expects students to type out the information on the slides while still taking notes while he speakes. His tests are hard
